#: src/bindings.md:1
msgid "Bindings"
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:3
msgid ""
"Maturin supports several kinds of bindings, some of which are automatically "
"detected. You can also pass `-b` / `--bindings` command line option to "
"manually specify which bindings to use."
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:7
msgid "`pyo3`"
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:9
msgid ""
"[pyo3](https://github.com/PyO3/pyo3) is Rust bindings for Python, including "
"tools for creating native Python extension modules. It supports CPython, "
"PyPy, and GraalPy."
msgstr ""
"[pyo3](https://github.com/PyO3/pyo3) 是 Python 的 Rust 綁定，包含用於建立原"
"生 Python 擴充模組的工具。它支援 CPython、PyPy 與 GraalPy。"

#: src/bindings.md:13
msgid ""
"maturin automatically detects pyo3 bindings when it's added as a dependency "
"in `Cargo.toml`."
msgstr ""
"當 `pyo3` 被增添為 `Cargo.toml` 中的依賴時，maturin 會自動偵測 pyo3 綁定。"

#: src/bindings.md:15
msgid "`Py_LIMITED_API`/abi3"
msgstr "`Py_LIMITED_API`/abi3"

#: src/bindings.md:17
msgid ""
"pyo3 bindings has `Py_LIMITED_API`/abi3 support, enable the `abi3` feature "
"of the `pyo3` crate to use it:"
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:19
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"pyo3 = { version = \"0.28.2\", features = [\"abi3\"] }\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"pyo3 = { version = \"0.28.2\", features = [\"abi3\"] }\n"
"```"

#: src/bindings.md:23
msgid ""
"You may additionally specify a minimum Python version by using the `abi3-"
"pyXX` format for the pyo3 features, where `XX` is corresponds to a Python "
"version. For example `abi3-py37` will indicate a minimum Python version of "
"3.7."
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:27
msgid ""
"**Note**: Read more about abi3 support in [pyo3's documentation](https://"
"pyo3.rs/latest/building-and-distribution#py_limited_apiabi3)."
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:30
msgid "Cross Compiling"
msgstr "交叉編譯"

#: src/bindings.md:32
msgid ""
"pyo3 bindings has decent cross compilation support. For manylinux support "
"the [manylinux-cross](https://github.com/rust-cross/manylinux-cross) docker "
"images can be used."
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:35
msgid ""
"**Note**: Read more about cross compiling in [pyo3's documentation](https://"
"pyo3.rs/latest/building-and-distribution#cross-compiling)."
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:38
msgid "`cffi`"
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:40
msgid ""
"Cffi wheels are compatible with all python versions including pypy. If "
"`cffi` isn't installed and python is running inside a virtualenv, maturin "
"will install it, otherwise you have to install it yourself (`pip install "
"cffi`)."
msgstr ""
"Cffi wheel 與包括 pypy 在內的所有 Python 版本相容。如果未安裝 `cffi` 且 "
"Python 是在虛擬環境（virtualenv）中執行，maturin 會自動安裝它，否則您必須自行"
"安裝（`pip install cffi`）。"

#: src/bindings.md:44
msgid ""
"Maturin uses cbindgen to generate a header file for [supported Rust types]"
"(https://github.com/eqrion/cbindgen/blob/master/docs.md#supported-types). "
"The header file can be customized by configuring cbindgen through a "
"`cbindgen.toml` file inside your project root. Aternatively you can use a "
"build script that writes a header file to `$PROJECT_ROOT/target/header.h`, "
"like so:"
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:56
msgid "\"CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR\""
msgstr "\"CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR\""

#: src/bindings.md:64
msgid "\"target\""
msgstr "\"target\""

#: src/bindings.md:64
msgid "\"header.h\""
msgstr "\"header.h\""

#: src/bindings.md:68
msgid ""
"Maturin uses the cbindgen-generated header to create a module that exposes "
"`ffi` and `lib` objects as attributes. See the [cffi docs](https://cffi."
"readthedocs.io/en/latest/using.html) for more information on using these "
"`ffi`/`lib` objects to call the Rust code from Python."
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:73
msgid ""
"**Note**: Maturin _does not_ automatically detect `cffi` bindings. You "
"_must_ specify them via either command line with `-b cffi` or in `pyproject."
"toml`."
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:76
msgid ""
"Maturin automatically detect `cffi` bindings, but only if there is no pyo3 "
"dependency. You can specify `cffi` explicitly via either command line with `-"
"b cffi` or in `pyproject.toml`."
msgstr ""
"maturin 會自動偵測 `cffi` 綁定，但前提是沒有 pyo3 依賴。您可以透過命令行引數 "
"`-b cffi` 或在 `pyproject.toml` 中明確指定 `cffi`。"

#: src/bindings.md:80
msgid "`bin`"
msgstr "`bin`"

#: src/bindings.md:82
msgid ""
"Maturin also supports distributing binary applications written in Rust as "
"Python packages using the `bin` bindings. Binaries are packaged into the "
"wheel as \"scripts\" and are available on the user's `PATH` (e.g. in the "
"`bin` directory of a virtual environment) once installed."
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:87
msgid ""
"Maturin automatically detect `bin` bindings, but only if there is only a "
"binary target and no pyo3 dependency or cdylib target. You can specify `bin` "
"explicitly via either command line with `-b bin` or in `pyproject.toml`."
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:91
msgid "Both binary and library?"
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:93
msgid ""
"Shipping both a binary and library would double the size of your wheel. "
"Consider instead exposing a CLI function in the library and using a Python "
"entrypoint:"
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:98
msgid ""
"// This one includes python and the name of the wrapper script itself, e.g.\n"
"    // `[\"/home/ferris/.venv/bin/python\", \"/home/ferris/.venv/bin/"
"print_cli_args\", \"a\", \"b\", \"c\"]`\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:100 src/bindings.md:104
msgid "\"{:?}\""
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:101
msgid ""
"// This one includes only the name of the wrapper script itself, e.g.\n"
"    // `[\"/home/ferris/.venv/bin/print_cli_args\", \"a\", \"b\", \"c\"])`\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/bindings.md:105
msgid "\"sys\""
msgstr "\"sys\""

#: src/bindings.md:106
msgid "\"argv\""
msgstr "\"argv\""

#: src/bindings.md:120
msgid "In pyproject.toml:"
msgstr "在 pyproject.toml 中："

#: src/bindings.md:122
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[project.scripts]\n"
"print_cli_args = \"my_module:print_cli_args\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"[project.scripts]\n"
"print_cli_args = \"my_module:print_cli_args\"\n"
"```"

#: src/bindings.md:127
msgid "`uniffi`"
msgstr "`uniffi`"

#: src/bindings.md:129
msgid ""
"uniffi bindings use [uniffi-rs](https://mozilla.github.io/uniffi-rs/) to "
"generate Python `ctypes` bindings from an interface definition file. uniffi "
"wheels are compatible with all python versions including pypy."
msgstr ""
"uniffi 綁定使用 [uniffi-rs](https://mozilla.github.io/uniffi-rs/) 從介面定義"
"檔生成 Python `ctypes` 綁定。uniffi 的 wheel 檔案與包括 pypy 在內的所有 "
"Python 版本相容。"
